column25: Interesting elements of funk combined with electronic sounds. A lot more stripped down than there debut album "In A Tidal Wave of Mystery", but a very similar sound overall.

Despite being have a clear pop punk sound, on some songs Something Corporate sounds closer to Mike Doughty of Soul Coughing than a true pop punk band. There is a more distinct use of piano melodies that come through the foreground that really separates Something Corporate from most pop punk and brings it in to a more Alternative Rock band with elements of pop punk.
